els: • Sustainability governance equating to 15% entitlement (i.e. 7.5% entitlement to the • Entry Level at APAT of $382 million, equating to 80% STI pool = $0.205 million) entitlement of the STI subject to the financial condition; • Governance, risk and compliance frameworks equating to 30% entitlement (i.e., • 100% Level at APAT of $455 million, equating to 100% 15% entitlement to the STI pool = $0.41 million). entitlement of the STI subject to the financial condition (i.e., Full achievement of the non-financial conditions will equate to 50% entitlement to the 50% entitlement to the 100% STI pool = $1.37 million); STI pool i.e., a total of $1.37 million. • Over-Achievement Level at APAT of $528 million, equating to 100% entitlement of the 100% STI Pool subject to the financial (c) Malus adjustments of up to 30% for non-achievement condition (i.e., 50% entitlement to the 100% STI pool = $1.37 million) and 100% entitlement to the Over-Achievement Pool The malus (financial penalty) provisions could reduce the overall achievement of the STI Amount of $0.64 million, resulting in a total Over-Achievement award by 30%, subject to the discretion of the Remuneration Committee to increase the entitlement of $2.01 million; malus penalty as appropriate. The malus provisions were made up of the following • Straight-line sliding scale for achievement of the 100% level, items: subject to achieving the Entry Level threshold; and • Work, health & safety governance framework = 10% of the 30% • Straight-line sliding scale for achievement between the 100% • Effective brand advertising compliance processes = 10% of the 30% Level and the Over-Achievement Level. • Appropriate governance, risk management and compliance framework activities = The Financial Condition settings were determined in line with 10% of the 30% internal expectations and consensus forecasts of external market The malus provisions could potentially reduce the overall achievement of the STI award analysts. The corrido