celebrating the resilience and generosity of regional Australia. In 2025, the Company launched a new initiative spotlighting three local heroes in each featured town. Through online and in-store promotions, communities nominated and voted for recipients of $2,000 Harvey Norman® gift cards. The campaign supported causes including cancer clinics, food pantries, women’s health, youth programs, animal welfare, and Indigenous pathways. GIANTS AFL & AFLW Good360 Australia Harvey Norman® remains a proud partner of the GIANTS men’s In FY25, Good360 celebrated a significant milestone, and women’s football programs. This partnership strengthens ties marking a decade of impactful work in Australia. Harvey with the Greater Western Sydney community through grassroots Norman® continued its support by donating brand-new initiatives and shared values. products to individuals facing hardship. Since 2019, the In 2025, the GIANTS AFLW team celebrated its 10th season. The members of the consolidated entity have helped over competition recorded strong growth, with 309,000 attendees (+8% 78,000 disadvantaged individuals across Australia. YoY) and a cumulative TV audience of 7.7 million (+17% YoY). During FY25, Harvey Norman® has donated $1.19 million worth of goods to more than 60 charities. “Harvey Norman® enables us to deliver essential goods to those in need. Their support helps restore dignity and deliver hope.” — Alison Covington AM, Founder, Good360 Harvey Norman® remains committed to addressing material deprivation through its partnership with Good360. The 2025 Home Impact Report highlights the significant strides Good360 has made in connecting over $2.6 million in donated household goods to Australians in need. “Every home should offer comfort and dignity. Our donations help families create safe, functional living spaces and provide a sense of security and hope.” — Katie Page, CEO, Harvey Norman® NRLW & NRL All Stars The NRLW Premiership expanded to 12 teams in 2025, including the Canterbury Bulldogs and the return of the One NZ Warriors. Harvey Norman® deepened its commitment by partnering with the Warriors to grow Women’s Rugby League in New Zealand. The 19th Women in League Round celebrated the evolving role of women in the sport, from players and referees to coaches and fans. The Women’s State of Origin broke attendance records with over 26,000 spectators and 2 million broadcast viewers. The Jillaroos also debuted in Las Vegas before a crowd of 45,000. Harvey Norman® continued as naming rights sponsor of the NRL All Stars. In 2025, the match returned to Western Sydney, accompanied by a week of cultural events, including the inaugural Cultural Storytelling Workshop led by Dean Widders. 63 Directors’ Report Sustainability Report (continued) Places The Harvey Norman® global footprint of franchised complexes To support the Places pillar, relevant controlled entities and and overseas company-operated stores underpins its integrated independent franchisees engage with the following organisations retail, franchise, property, and digital strategy. With 195 franchised to advance environmental and social responsibility: complexes in Australia and 121 company-operated stores across • Energy Users Association of Australia seven international markets, Harvey Norman® continues to invest in modern, customer-centric retail environments that reflect its • National Retailers Association commitment to quality and innovation. • Australian Bedding Stewardship Council The physical footprint is central to both commercial performance • Consumer Electronics Association and sustainability goals. The ongoing refit program ensures stores remain energy-efficient, contemporary, and compliant • Australian Packaging Covenant with evolving environmental standards. Regular maintenance • Retail Excellence Ireland and upgrades enhance operational efficiency and customer experience. • Retail NZ’s Sustainability Group Warehouse infrastructure is also designed with sustainab